sentences.english: He was anointed princeps ; the Roman empire is said to begin with his accession.
sentences.chinese: 他被奉爲元首，羅馬帝國據說就是從他即位開始。

sentences.english: He may have been influenced by the prophet Isaiah whose ministry covered much of Hezekiah's reign.
sentences.chinese: 以賽亞主要是在希西家在位年間作先知的事奉。

sentences.english: By the orders of the deputy procureur?

sentences.english: I have cast out demons from a number of people.
sentences.chinese: 我曾奉耶穌名替多人趕邪靈。

sentences.english: Now we are entering the third and final year of His earthly ministry.
sentences.chinese: 如今我們進入祂在世事奉的第三年，也是最後一年。

sentences.english: Leading the effort today are Western-oriented leaders who are almost uniformly young.
sentences.chinese: 現今領導羣倫的都是清一色奉西方爲圭臬的年輕人。

sentences.english: As for the word that thou hast spoken unto us in the name of the LORD, we will not hearken unto thee.
sentences.chinese: 論到你奉耶和華的名向我們所說的話，我們必不聽從。

sentences.english: Did you shy away from full-hearted service for the sake of Christ?

sentences.english: Family counselors remind parents not to take what a child says as the gospel truth.

sentences.english: Give Him first place in your service, consecrate every part.
sentences.chinese: 支配你一切的事奉，每部分因主成聖。

sentences.english: Had he ever served in the temple?

sentences.english: Please remember brother Eric Lin's ministry in your prayers.
sentences.chinese: 請弟兄姊妹爲林春騰弟兄的事奉禱告。

sentences.english: Serve the Lord your God, so that his fierce anger will turn away from you.
sentences.chinese: 又要事奉耶和華你們的神，好使他的烈怒轉離你們。
